{
  "text": "Treatment interruptions and dose reductions (to 120 mg, then 80 mg) were allowed to manage toxicity (appendix pp [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . The regorafenib dose could be reescalated to a maximum of 160 mg at the investigator's discretion once toxicities were resolved. If further dose reduction was required, treatment was discontinued.",
